node.text:
To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.text: A modern take on the Peachtree Punch, Martin Cate rejiggered the 1970s Trader Vic recipe one ingredient at a time. Fresh peaches and housemade coconut cream replace their canned alternatives, while natural peach liqueur stands in for schnapps and lemon juice is added for an extra jolt of acidity. Check out the full recipe for his remake of the classic tiki drink via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @aubrieprick

node.text: We went searching for the ultimate Negroni Sbagliato—sweet vermouth, Italian bitters, and sparkling wine—and we found it, well, them, actually. Our panel of experts blind-tasted nearly a dozen recipes from America’s top bartenders to find the perfect version. Ultimately, two recipes tied for first place. Find out which bartenders took home top honors and get the winning recipes via the link in our profile #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text:
Margaritas get all the attention, but @joshgoldman2 prefers to celebrate another agave all-star: the Paloma. “It’s such a great framework for a cocktail,” he says. “The flavors go with just about anything. It’s bulletproof.” Over the years, he’s created multiple versions of the sweet-tart classic, a highball typically made with tequila, grapefruit soda and a squeeze of lime. His classic version, which took a top spot in a PUNCH blind tasting, tops tequila and fresh lime with Squirt, a wedge of grapefruit and a pinch of salt, but his roster of nontraditional versions shows just how versatile the Paloma blueprint can be. Head to the link in our profile for four plays on the effervescent agave-grapefruit template. #drinkpunch 📷: @dylanandjeni ⁠

node.text: Is the 50/50 Even a Martini? For some the fashionably wet iteration of the Martini that calls for equal parts gin and dry vermouth is the original incarnation of the famously austere cocktail. By others, it’s not a Martini at all. Where do you fall on the 50/50 divide? Leave your go-to Martini specs below. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text:
Over the span of three decades, the Cosmopolitan went from becoming the bold-faced darling of the New York bar scene to facing an inevitable retreat, to eventually returning for a star-studded second act as a certified modern classic. And this fall, Cointreau (@cointreau_us #punchpartner) will continue to support the recovering restaurant and bar community through Cosmos for a Cause, a charitable program in partnership with @indprestaurants. ⁠
Head to the link in our profile for bartenders on why they’re welcoming the great Cosmo revival and to sign your bar or restaurant up to participate in Cosmos for a Cause.⁠
#cosmosforacause⁠
📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: In 2006, few people in the United States understood the appeal of gin or pastis. @audreysaunders’ rather counterintuitive solution to this problem was to put both the gin and the pastis in the same shaken drink—along with lime juice, simple syrup and mint leaves. She called it the French Pearl. In recent years, the unusual cocktail has developed a reputation as a kind of unsung classic, a @peguclub_nyc staple that got somewhat buried and lost under all the praise heaped on better-known Saunders drinks like the Old Cuban, Gin-Gin Mule and Little Italy. Head to the link in our profile where @robertosimonson cements its status as a modern classic. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Have you ever had a Rebujito? The storied, eminently refreshing, Andalusian sherry highball is primed for a breakout. A delicious and complex blend of lemon-lime soda, fino or manzanilla sherry and ice, the populist drink is the stuff of Andalusian legend, fueling hot nights of summer revelry in the Sherry Triangle. As a low-ABV, two-ingredient cocktail with overseas cool factor and endless riffing potential, the Rebujito is ready for its stateside close-up. Head to the link in our profile where @suitcasewine dives into the history of the drink and the bartenders riffing on it today. 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Kümmel is typically found in shaken, citrusy drinks, but @ali.scotch has found a new home for the complex spirit, whose taste he describes as ranging from white chocolate to pink peppercorn to olive tapenade to walnut. Here, he simply stirs it with Campari and aged rum, where the olive flavors from Ron Zacapa 23 complement the caraway and chocolate notes from kümmel. Check out the recipe for The Night Shining via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: The Mid-Morning Fizz is the perfect summer eye-opener. This RGF variation loses the cream of the original recipe and adds green Chartreuse for a more pronounced spiciness. Light but complex, it's a time-tested hangover cure. Head to the link in our profile for the recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: The Old Haitian is a Mojito, twice removed. @audreysaunders first transformed the classic into an Old Cuban and @orlandofranklin took it one step further. Here, he for opts for clairin, a Haitian rhum agricole, and builds upon it with mint, lime, dry Curaçao and Champagne. Served over crushed ice, rather than up in coupe, it's a summer crusher. Check out the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro
